Currently nothing in the code uses `IAggregateRoot`. One way to have the code better enforce the DDD convention that only Aggregate Roots should have Repositories would be to implement a generic repository type. Since our repositories aren't implementing any standard set of CRUD methods (currently it just exposes UnitOfWork) the change could simply be like this, in IAggregateRepository:

```
    public interface IAggregateRepository<T> where T:IAggregateRoot
    {
        IUnitOfWork UnitOfWork { get; }
    }
```

It's worth considering that `IAggregateRepository` is redundant as a name at that point. Since the rule is that only Aggregates (their roots) have repositories, the interface can simply be `IRepository`.
